<br>
Dubar laughed as they raced through the woods at amazing speeds.  &quot;Aye, love, yer right an I was wrong to make light of it.  But at least we're in for some fun!&quot;  He'd long felt that he wasn't really having fun unless he was within an inch of death.  The Paladin laughed long and loud, &quot;You know, this one might be quite a fight.&quot;<br>
<br>
They ran on into the forest for several minutes before finally stopping.  &quot;I don't hear anything anymore...&quot;  Lyrnia said.  &quot;It's like they vanished.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, I don't pretend to understand it either.  It's very odd.  Nothing kills people that fast... nothing&quot;, Dubar said with a worried look.  After a moment of silence he began praying to his godess, Erollisi Marr, and mystic energies surrounded the two of them, shielding them from danger and granting them courage to face what might come.  Motioning for her to wait, he headed out for a brief scout of the area.  Lyrnia sighed and sat down to wait.<br>
<br>
After a while he returned, having found nothing.  &quot;I wish Megadyen were here.&quot;<br>
<br>
Lyrnia smiled at the mention of their friend.  A mighty ranger, Megdyen spent most of his time on Faydwer hunting the evils of Unrest and Mistmoore.  &quot;I'm sure he misses us too.  I wish Linc were here though.  I think we may be in over our heads.  Maybe we should go meet him, then come back to investigate this?&quot;<br>
<br>
Dubar nodded his agreement and the two of them returned to their camp.  Laying down to sleep he smiled up at his elven companion.  &quot;I know you don't need sleep, Lyrnia, but wake me up for my shift please?&quot;<br>
<br>
Lyrnia laughed.  It had long been an aggravation of Dubar's that she often stayed awake for days at a time without rest.  Her bardic gift keeping her energised beyond the means of others.  Humming a quiet tune she said, &quot;I may, we might need you fully refreshed though, so I may not.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well then,&quot; with that he lay down and tried to sleep.  <br>
<br>
Smiling fondly at her companion, and her love, Lyrnia thought back to their youth and smiled when remembering how she'd met him and his brother so long ago in the desert of Ro, nearly dead, and fighting for their lives.  Many times since then the three had travelled, meeting many companions and friends along the way.  They had saved each others lives more times than could ever be counted and had become fast friends and companions.  Dubar was... something more... though he'd never said anything she knew he was in love with her as well.  &lt;i&gt;If only he would say something to me about it&lt;/i&gt; she thought to herself silently.  &lt;i&gt;He should know by now that my answer would be yes... and with the times of terror coming... well... enough moongazing time to stand watch&lt;i&gt;.  Lyrnia rose, still humming her tune of refreshment, began patrolling around the camp till morning...<br>
